ENTRY       EC 4.4.1.22                 Enzyme
NAME        S-(hydroxymethyl)glutathione synthase;
            glutathione-dependent formaldehyde-activating enzyme;
            Gfa;
            S-(hydroxymethyl)glutathione formaldehyde-lyase
CLASS       Lyases;
            Carbon-sulfur lyases;
            Carbon-sulfur lyases (only sub-subclass identified to date)
SYSNAME     S-(hydroxymethyl)glutathione formaldehyde-lyase (glutathione-forming)
REACTION    S-(hydroxymethyl)glutathione = glutathione + formaldehyde [RN:R06982]
ALL_REAC    R06982
SUBSTRATE   S-(hydroxymethyl)glutathione [CPD:C14180]
PRODUCT     glutathione [CPD:C00051];
            formaldehyde [CPD:C00067]
COMMENT     The enzyme from Paracoccus denitrificans accelerates the spontaneous reaction in which the adduct of formaldehyde and glutathione is formed, i.e. the substrate for EC 1.1.1.284, S-(hydroxymethyl)glutathione dehydrogenase, in the formaldehyde-detoxification pathway.
